                <p>Where:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>F =3D Final exam grade</li>
                    <li>G =3D Grade you want for the class</li>
                    <li>w =3D % weight of the final exam divided by 100, wh=
ich is simply weight as a decimal</li>
                    <li>C =3D Your current grade</li>
                </ul>
                <p>This is the math to calculate the final grade you want t=
o achieve:</p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Divide weight of the final exam by 100 to get weigh=
t as a decimal, <em>w</em>.</li>
                    <li>Find the innermost parentheses: subtract <em>w</em>=
 from 1.</li>
                    <li>Find the next set of parentheses: multiply the resu=
lt from step two by
                        <em>C</em>, your current grade.
                    </li>
                    <li>Subtract the result of step 3 from <em>G</em>, the =
grade you want for the class.</li>
                    <li>Divide this by <em>w</em>. The result is the grade =
you need on the final exam.</li>
                </ol>
                <p>The final grade calculation might seem like a lot, but i=
t=E2=80=99s not hard. Start with the math in the innermost parentheses, 1 =
=E2=80=93
                    <em>w</em>. This means subtract the weight of the final=
 as a decimal from 1.</p>
                <p>The second step is to look at the next level of parenthe=
ses. Multiply your first result by
                    <em>C</em>, your course grade entering the final.</p>
                <p>Next, subtract this result from
                    <em>G</em>, the grade you would like for the course. Fi=
nally, divide by <em>w</em>.</p>
                <p>The result is the score you need on the final exam to re=
ach your goal grade in this subject.</p>
